    import pandas as pd
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    import seaborn as sns

    # Load the dataset
    df = pd.read_csv(r"C:\Users\chero\Downloads\archive.zip")

    # Check the columns in the dataset
    print(df.columns)

    # Preview the first 5 rows of the dataset
    print(df.head())

    # Identify missing values in each column
    print(df.isnull().sum())

    location = ['Kenya', 'USA', 'India']
    df_filtered = df[df['location'].isin(location)]

    critical_columns = ['date', 'total_cases', 'total_deaths']
    df_cleaned = df.dropna(subset=critical_columns)
    print(df_cleaned.isnull().sum)

    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])
    df['total_cases'] = df['total_cases'].interpolate(method='linear')
    df['total_deaths'] = df['total_deaths'].interpolate(method='linear')


    df_grouped = df_filtered.groupby(['date', 'location'])['total_cases'].sum().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=df_grouped, x='date', y='total_cases', hue='location', marker='o')

    # Adding labels and title
    plt.title('Total Cases Over Time for Selected Countries')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Total Cases')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='location')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()

    df_deaths_grouped = df_filtered.groupby(['date', 'location'])['total_deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    # Adding labels and title
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=df_deaths_grouped, x='date', y='total_deaths', hue='location', marker='o')

    plt.title('Total Deaths Over Time for Selected Countries')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Total Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='location')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()

    # Show plot
    plt.show()

    df_filtered['new_cases'] = df_filtered['new_cases'].fillna(0)
    df_new_cases_grouped = df_filtered.groupby(['date', 'location'])['new_cases'].sum().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=df_new_cases_grouped, x='date', y='new_cases', hue='location', marker='o')

    plt.title('Daily New Cases Comparison Between Countries')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('New Cases')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='location')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()

    # Show plot
    plt.show()

    df_total_cases_by_country = df.groupby('location')['total_cases'].sum().reset_index()

    # Sort by total cases in descending order
    df_total_cases_by_country = df_total_cases_by_country.sort_values(by='total_cases', ascending=False)

    # Plot the bar chart for top countries by total cases
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(data=df_total_cases_by_country, x='location', y='total_cases', palette='viridis')
